John Christopher Hawken (born 9 May 1940 in Bournemouth) is an English keyboard player.
He studied classical piano between the ages of four and eighteen before acquiring a taste for rock and roll.
Hawken's first band was the Cruisers Rock Combo (1960 to 1962) but he is possibly best known for his contributions to various versions of The Nashville Teens (1962 to 1968).
